From: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: force XGMAC TX queue 0 store-and-forward

Observed on IPQ5332 XGMAC ports, small outbound packets increment
tx_underflow_err unless MTL queue 0 is forced into store-and-forward
mode. Program the TSF bit before enabling transmission so the queue
is drained only after the frame has been buffered.

Signed-off-by: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe_port.c | 8 ++++++++
 drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe_regs.h | 3 +++
 2 files changed, 11 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe_port.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe_port.c
@@ -770,6 +770,15 @@ static int ppe_port_xgmac_link_up(struct
 	}
 
 	reg = PPE_PORT_XGMAC_ADDR(port);
+	/*
+	 * Use store-and-forward for XGMAC MTL queue 0 so transmission
+	 * starts only after the frame has been buffered.
+	 */
+	ret = regmap_update_bits(ppe_dev->regmap, reg + XGMAC_MTL_TXQ_OPMODE(0),
+				 XGMAC_MTL_TXQ_TSF, XGMAC_MTL_TXQ_TSF);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
 	val |= XGMAC_TXEN;
 	ret = regmap_update_bits(ppe_dev->regmap, reg + XGMAC_TX_CONFIG_ADDR,
 				 XGMAC_SPEED_M | XGMAC_TXEN, val);
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe_regs.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe_regs.h
@@ -695,6 +695,10 @@
 #define XGMAC_JD				BIT(16)
 #define XGMAC_TXEN				BIT(0)
 
+/* XGMAC MTL Tx queue operating mode register */
+#define XGMAC_MTL_TXQ_OPMODE(_q)		(0x00001100 + (0x80 * (_q)))
+#define XGMAC_MTL_TXQ_TSF			BIT(1)
+
 /* XGMAC RX configuration register */
 #define XGMAC_RX_CONFIG_ADDR			0x4
 #define XGMAC_GPSL_M				GENMASK(29, 16)
